'''Joke Fincioen''' is a Belgian-born United States-based television producer, filmmaker, director, and [[showrunner]]. She pronounces her first name /jōk/.<ref name=PDSQ>{{cite news|last1=Simakis|first1=Andrea|title='Scream Queens' helps Parma native make it big in Hollywood|url=http://www.cleveland.com/tv/index.ssf/2010/10/scream_queens_helps_parma_nati.html|accessdate=28 January 2016|work=[[The Plain Dealer]]|date=10 October 2010}}</ref> Her television credits include the [[VH1]] reality TV acting competition series [[Scream Queens (2008 TV series)|''Scream Queens'']],<ref name=THRSQ>{{cite news|last1=Nordyke|first1=Kimberly|title=Reality series looks to cast actress in horror film|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/vh1-greenlights-scream-queens-113391|accessdate=January 28, 2016|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=8 June 2008}}</ref> the [[MTV]] documentary series [[Caged (TV series)|''Caged'']],<ref name=VarietyCaged>{{cite news|last1=Levine|first1=Stuart|title=New series on teens who engage in MMA begins Jan. 9|url=https://variety.com/2011/tv/news/mtv-sets-debut-date-for-caged-1118046857|accessdate=28 January 2016|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=1 December 2011}}</ref> [[The CW]] social experiment ''[[Beauty and the Geek]]'',<ref name="PDSQ"/> and the MTV ''[[True Life]]'' ''Presents'' documentary feature [[List of True Life episodes#Season 16 .282013.29|''Secrets, Lies, and Sex'']].<ref name=JokeSLS>{{cite web|title=True Life Presents: Secrets, Lies, and Sex|url=http://jokeproductions.com/true-life-presents-secrets-lies-and-sex|website=Joke Productions|accessdate=28 January 2016}}</ref>  

Her filmmaking credits include the theatrically released, feature-length documentary ''[[Dying to do Letterman]]'', which was invited by the [[International Documentary Association]] to qualify for Academy Award consideration.<ref name=IWKick>{{cite news|title=The 21 Secrets to the Success of the Kickstarter Oscar Campaign|url=http://www.indiewire.com/article/the_21_secrets_to_the_success_of_the_kickstarter_oscar_campaign|accessdate=15 January 2016|work=[[Indiewire]]|date=11 July 2011}}</ref>  She has produced and contributed to over one-hundred hours of TV and film.<ref name=AboutJokeProd>{{cite web|title=About Joke Productions|url=http://jokeproductions.com/about/|website=Joke Productions|accessdate=28 January 2016}}</ref>

