{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2014}} {{Infobox book | name = Noureddin, Son of Iran | title_orig = | translator = | image = Noureddin, Son of Iran cover book.jpg | author = Masoume Sepehri | cover_artist = | country = Iran | language = [[Persian language|Persian]] | series = | genre = Memoir | publisher = Sureye Mehr Publication | release_date = 2011 | media_type = Book | pages = 700 | isbn = 978-600-175-220-9 }}
'''''Noureddin, Son of Iran''''' ({{lang-fa|نورالدین پسر ایران}}) is the memoirs of [[Sayyid]] Noureddin Afi from the 80 months of his participation in the [[Iran–Iraq war]]. ''Noureddin, Son of Iran'' led to Afi's reputation in Iran after it was published by Sureye Mehr Publication in 2011. In 1994, Mousa Ghayour recorded the memoirs of Noureddin Afi in [[Turkish language|Turkish]] and it was presented as a written book by Masoume Sepehri years later. َThis book consisted of 18 chapters along with photographs.<ref>[http://www.ibna.ir/vdcauwn6y49nia1.tgk4.html Iran Book News Agency]</ref> The narrator mentions a dream as the reason of producing this war memoir.<ref name="Mashregh">{{cite web |url=http://www.mashreghnews.ir/fa/news/117519/%D9%86%D9%88%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AF%DB%8C%D9%86-%D9%BE%D8%B3%D8%B1-%D8%A7%DB%8C%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%AE%D8%A7%D8%B7%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D9%85%D8%B1%D8%AF%DB%8C-%D9%83%D9%87-%D9%81%D9%83%D8%B1-%D9%85%DB%8C%E2%80%8C%D9%83%D8%B1%D8%AF-%D9%83%D8%A7%D8%B1%DB%8C-%D9%86%D9%83%D8%B1%D8%AF%D9%87-%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%AA |title= "Noureddin, Son of Iran" The memoir of a man who believed he had done nothing|author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date= |website= Mashreghnews.com |publisher= |accessdate= 4 June 2014 }}</ref> ''Noureddin, Son of Iran'' received an honorable menion in the "Memoir" category of the [[Jalal Al-e Ahmad Literary Awards]] (2012).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tehrantimes.com/arts-and-culture/103523-no-winner-selected-for-irans-most-lucrative-literary-awards-this-year |title=No winner selected for Iran’s most lucrative literary awards this year |work=[[Tehran Times]] |date=25 November 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121210083837/http://www.tehrantimes.com/arts-and-culture/103523-no-winner-selected-for-irans-most-lucrative-literary-awards-this-year |archivedate=10 December 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>
==Narrative== [[Sayyid]] Noureddin wants to participate the Iran–Iraq war, but he is not allowed at first because he is still young. He tries repeatedly and finally they let him go to war. He attends a military training course in the fall of 1980, and heads toward the western zones of Iran to serve in the [[Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps|Sepah]] of the [[Mehabad]]. He moves to the southern war zones along with his brother, Sadegh. Nourreddin loses his brother in an Iraqi [[airstrike]]. With shrapnel in his body they make him go under surgery in the hospitals of [[Mashhad]] and [[Kermanshah]] many times. But he does not recover well because he is severely damaged in the face, eyes and stomach. Due to the severe injuries on his face, his countenance changes when he is only 18. In 1984, he marries a 16-year-old girl named Masoume and their child is born 4 years later. The war finishes but he is still suffering the injuries and he misses his lovely friends, especially Amir Maralbash who was killed in the war.<ref>[http://manvaketab.ir/145079-نورالدین-پسر-ایران/bz=fs Book introduction, Nourreddin, Son of Iran (Persian)]</ref>
==Why it was written== In the last page of his memoir, Afi expresses his motivation for recounting his war memories as such: {{quote|I never thought that, telling the memories is important nowadays. However, war memories and interviews were not discussed and I was involved with the side effects my injuries. In 1994, I dreamed that Mr [[Khamenei]] was reading some papers and crying. I was there, Some one said that these papers were the memories of a %70 [[veteran]] who had participated in war for 80 months and still said he had nothing for the war...My mind was busy with this dream and I felt my duty would finish by telling these memories. So, I recounted the eight years of living in the war context to make those unique times survive for ever. (P632)<ref name="Mashregh"/>}}
==Animated movie==
''Noureddin, Son of Iran'' is a [[Computer animation|computer animated]] movie directed by Meisam Hosseini. The movie consists of 30 parts of 15 minutes each. Famous Iranian artists such as Atila Pesyani, [[Pejman Bazeghi]], Ali Saleh Ala and Masoud Forutan worked on the movie.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mehrnews.com/detail/News/2136101 |title= "Noureddin, Son of Iran" with the voice of Iranian famous artists/from Saleh Ala and Pesyani to Bazeghi and Forutan|author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date= |website= mehrnews.com/ Mehr News |publisher= |accessdate= 4 June 2014 }}</ref>
